106static BitArray::Range
107FindNextPair(const BitArray& row, const std::list<ExpandedPair>& previousPairs, int forcedOffset, bool startFromEven, FinderCounters& counters)
108{
109 int rowOffset;
110 if (forcedOffset >= 0) {
111 rowOffset = forcedOffset;
112 }
113 else if (previousPairs.empty()) {
114 rowOffset = 0;
115 }
116 else {
117 rowOffset = previousPairs.back().finderPattern().endPos();
118 }
119 bool searchingEvenPair = previousPairs.size() % 2 != 0;
120 if (startFromEven) {
121 searchingEvenPair = !searchingEvenPair;
122 }
123
124 return RowReader::FindPattern(
125 // find
126 row.getNextSet(row.iterAt(rowOffset)), row.end(), counters,
127 [searchingEvenPair](BitArray::Iterator, BitArray::Iterator, FinderCounters& counters) {
128 if (ReaderHelper::IsFinderPatternExtended(counters, searchingEvenPair)) {
129 if (searchingEvenPair)
130 std::reverse(counters.begin(), counters.end());
131 return true;
132 }
133 return false;
134 });
135}
136
137static FinderPattern
138ParseFoundFinderPattern(const BitArray& row, int rowNumber, bool oddPattern, BitArray::Range range, FinderCounters& counters) {
139 // Actually we found elements 2-5.
140 int firstCounter;
141
142 if (oddPattern) {
143 // If pattern number is odd, we need to locate element 1 *before* the current block.
144
145 auto i = std::find(BitArray::ReverseIterator(range.begin), row.rend(), *range.begin);
146 firstCounter = static_cast<int>(range.begin - i.base());
147 range.begin = i.base();
148 }
149 else {
150 // If pattern number is even, the pattern is reversed, so we need to locate element 1 *after* the current block.
151
152 auto i = row.getNextUnset(std::next(range.end)); // +1?
153 firstCounter = static_cast<int>(i - range.end);
154 range.end = i;
155 }
156
157 int start = static_cast<int>(range.begin - row.begin());
158 int end = static_cast<int>(range.end - row.begin());
159
160 // Make 'counters' hold 1-4
161 std::copy_backward(counters.begin(), counters.end() - 1, counters.end());
162 counters[0] = firstCounter;
163 int value = ReaderHelper::ParseFinderValue(counters, FINDER_PATTERNS);
164 if (value < 0)
165 return {};
166
167 return {value, start, end, {ResultPoint(start, rowNumber), ResultPoint(end, rowNumber)}};
168}
169
170static bool
171IsNotA1left(FinderPattern pattern, bool isOddPattern, bool leftChar)
172{
173 // A1: pattern.getValue is 0 (A), and it's an oddPattern, and it is a left char
174 return !(pattern.value() == 0 && isOddPattern && leftChar);
175}
176
177static bool
178AdjustOddEvenCounts(int numModules, std::array<int, 4>& oddCounts, std::array<int, 4>& evenCounts, const std::array<float, 4>& oddRoundingErrors, const std::array<float, 4>& evenRoundingErrors)
179{
180 int oddSum = std::accumulate(oddCounts.begin(), oddCounts.end(), 0);
181 int evenSum = std::accumulate(evenCounts.begin(), evenCounts.end(), 0);
182 int mismatch = oddSum + evenSum - numModules;
183 bool oddParityBad = (oddSum & 0x01) == 1;
184 bool evenParityBad = (evenSum & 0x01) == 0;
185
186 bool incrementOdd = false;
187 bool decrementOdd = false;
188
189 if (oddSum > 13) {
190 decrementOdd = true;
191 }
192 else if (oddSum < 4) {
193 incrementOdd = true;
194 }
195 bool incrementEven = false;
196 bool decrementEven = false;
197 if (evenSum > 13) {
198 decrementEven = true;
199 }
200 else if (evenSum < 4) {
201 incrementEven = true;
202 }
203
204 if (mismatch == 1) {
205 if (oddParityBad) {
206 if (evenParityBad) {
207 return false;
208 }
209 decrementOdd = true;
210 }
211 else {
212 if (!evenParityBad) {
213 return false;
214 }
215 decrementEven = true;
216 }
217 }
218 else if (mismatch == -1) {
219 if (oddParityBad) {
220 if (evenParityBad) {
221 return false;
222 }
223 incrementOdd = true;
224 }
225 else {
226 if (!evenParityBad) {
227 return false;
228 }
229 incrementEven = true;
230 }
231 }
232 else if (mismatch == 0) {
233 if (oddParityBad) {
234 if (!evenParityBad) {
235 return false;
236 }
237 // Both bad
238 if (oddSum < evenSum) {
239 incrementOdd = true;
240 decrementEven = true;
241 }
242 else {
243 decrementOdd = true;
244 incrementEven = true;
245 }
246 }
247 else {
248 if (evenParityBad) {
249 return false;
250 }
251 // Nothing to do!
252 }
253 }
254 else {
255 return false;
256 }
257
258 if (incrementOdd) {
259 if (decrementOdd) {
260 return false;
261 }
262 oddCounts[std::max_element(oddRoundingErrors.begin(), oddRoundingErrors.end()) - oddRoundingErrors.begin()] += 1;
263 }
264 if (decrementOdd) {
265 oddCounts[std::min_element(oddRoundingErrors.begin(), oddRoundingErrors.end()) - oddRoundingErrors.begin()] -= 1;
266 }
267 if (incrementEven) {
268 if (decrementEven) {
269 return false;
270 }
271 //evenCounts[std::max_element(oddRoundingErrors.begin(), oddRoundingErrors.end()) - oddRoundingErrors.begin()] += 1; // This is according to Java's code, but likely a bug!
272 evenCounts[std::max_element(evenRoundingErrors.begin(), evenRoundingErrors.end()) - evenRoundingErrors.begin()] += 1;
273 }
274 if (decrementEven) {
275 evenCounts[std::min_element(evenRoundingErrors.begin(), evenRoundingErrors.end()) - evenRoundingErrors.begin()] -= 1;
276 }
277 return true;
278}

280static DataCharacter
281DecodeDataCharacter(const BitArray& row, const FinderPattern& pattern, bool isOddPattern, bool leftChar)
282{
283 std::array<int, 8> counters = {};
284
285 if (leftChar) {
286 if (!RowReader::RecordPatternInReverse(row.begin(), row.iterAt(pattern.startPos()), counters))
287 return {};
288 }
289 else {
290 if (!RowReader::RecordPattern(row.iterAt(pattern.endPos()), row.end(), counters))
291 return {};
292 std::reverse(counters.begin(), counters.end());
293 }
294
295 int numModules = 17; //left and right data characters have all the same length
296 float elementWidth = static_cast<float>(std::accumulate(counters.begin(), counters.end(), 0)) / static_cast<float>(numModules);
297
298 // Sanity check: element width for pattern and the character should match
299 float expectedElementWidth = static_cast<float>(pattern.endPos() - pattern.startPos()) / 15.0f;
300 if (std::abs(elementWidth - expectedElementWidth) / expectedElementWidth > 0.3f) {
301 return {};
302 }
303
304 std::array<int, 4> oddCounts;
305 std::array<int, 4> evenCounts;
306 std::array<float, 4> oddRoundingErrors;
307 std::array<float, 4> evenRoundingErrors;
308
309 for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
310 float value = 1.0f * counters[i] / elementWidth;
311 int count = (int)(value + 0.5f); // Round
312 if (count < 1) {
313 if (value < 0.3f) {
314 return {};
315 }
316 count = 1;
317 }
318 else if (count > 8) {
319 if (value > 8.7f) {
320 return {};
321 }
322 count = 8;
323 }
324 int offset = i / 2;
325 if ((i & 0x01) == 0) {
326 oddCounts[offset] = count;
327 oddRoundingErrors[offset] = value - count;
328 }
329 else {
330 evenCounts[offset] = count;
331 evenRoundingErrors[offset] = value - count;
332 }
333 }
334
335 if (!AdjustOddEvenCounts(numModules, oddCounts, evenCounts, oddRoundingErrors, evenRoundingErrors)) {
336 return {};
337 }
338
339 int weightRowNumber = 4 * pattern.value() + (isOddPattern ? 0 : 2) + (leftChar ? 0 : 1) - 1;
340
341 int oddSum = 0;
342 int oddChecksumPortion = 0;
343 for (int i = 3; i >= 0; i--) {
344 if (IsNotA1left(pattern, isOddPattern, leftChar)) {
345 int weight = WEIGHTS[weightRowNumber][2 * i];
346 oddChecksumPortion += oddCounts[i] * weight;
347 }
348 oddSum += oddCounts[i];
349 }
350 int evenChecksumPortion = 0;
351 //int evenSum = 0;
352 for (int i = 3; i >= 0; i--) {
353 if (IsNotA1left(pattern, isOddPattern, leftChar)) {
354 int weight = WEIGHTS[weightRowNumber][2 * i + 1];
355 evenChecksumPortion += evenCounts[i] * weight;
356 }
357 //evenSum += evenCounts[i];
358 }
359 int checksumPortion = oddChecksumPortion + evenChecksumPortion;
360
361 if ((oddSum & 0x01) != 0 || oddSum > 13 || oddSum < 4) {
362 return {};
363 }
364
365 int group = (13 - oddSum) / 2;
366 int oddWidest = SYMBOL_WIDEST[group];
367 int evenWidest = 9 - oddWidest;
368 int vOdd = ReaderHelper::GetRSSvalue(oddCounts, oddWidest, true);
369 int vEven = ReaderHelper::GetRSSvalue(evenCounts, evenWidest, false);
370 int tEven = EVEN_TOTAL_SUBSET[group];
371 int gSum = GSUM[group];
372 int value = vOdd * tEven + vEven + gSum;
373
374 return {value, checksumPortion};
375}

377// not private for testing
378static bool
379RetrieveNextPair(const BitArray& row, const std::list<ExpandedPair>& previousPairs, int rowNumber, bool startFromEven, ExpandedPair& outPair)
380{
381 bool isOddPattern = previousPairs.size() % 2 == 0;
382 if (startFromEven) {
383 isOddPattern = !isOddPattern;
384 }
385
386 FinderPattern pattern;
387 bool keepFinding = true;
388 int forcedOffset = -1;
389 do {
390 FinderCounters counters = {};
391 auto range = FindNextPair(row, previousPairs, forcedOffset, startFromEven, counters);
392 if (!range)
393 return false;
394
395 pattern = ParseFoundFinderPattern(row, rowNumber, isOddPattern, range, counters);
396 if (!pattern.isValid()) {
397 // goto next bar of same color than current position
398 range.begin = row.getNextSetTo(range.begin, !*range.begin);
399 range.begin = row.getNextSetTo(range.begin, !*range.begin);
400 forcedOffset = static_cast<int>(range.begin - row.begin());
401 }
402 else {
403 keepFinding = false;
404 }
405 } while (keepFinding);
406
407 // When stacked symbol is split over multiple rows, there's no way to guess if this pair can be last or not.
408 // boolean mayBeLast = checkPairSequence(previousPairs, pattern);
409
410 DataCharacter leftChar = DecodeDataCharacter(row, pattern, isOddPattern, true);
411 if (!leftChar.isValid() || (!previousPairs.empty() && previousPairs.back().mustBeLast())) {
412 return false;
413 }
414
415 DataCharacter rightChar = DecodeDataCharacter(row, pattern, isOddPattern, false);
416 bool mayBeLast = true;
417 outPair = ExpandedPair(leftChar, rightChar, pattern, mayBeLast);
418 return true;
419}
420
421static bool
422CheckChecksum(const std::list<ExpandedPair>& myPairs)
423{
424 if (myPairs.empty())
425 return false;
426
427 auto& firstPair = myPairs.front();
428
429 if (firstPair.mustBeLast()) {
430 return false;
431 }
432
433 int checksum = firstPair.rightChar().checksumPortion();
434 int s = 2;
435
436 for (auto it = ++myPairs.begin(); it != myPairs.end(); ++it) {
437 checksum += it->leftChar().checksumPortion();
438 s++;
439 auto& currentRightChar = it->rightChar();
440 if (currentRightChar.isValid()) {
441 checksum += currentRightChar.checksumPortion();
442 s++;
443 }
444 }
445 checksum %= 211;
446 int checkCharacterValue = 211 * (s - 4) + checksum;
447 return checkCharacterValue == firstPair.leftChar().value();
448}

451// Returns true when one of the rows already contains all the pairs
452static bool
453IsPartialRow(const std::list<ExpandedPair>& pairs, const std::list<ExpandedRow>& rows) {
454 for (const ExpandedRow& r : rows) {
455 bool allFound = true;
456 for (const ExpandedPair& p : pairs) {
457 bool found = false;
458 for (const ExpandedPair& pp : r.pairs()) {
459 if (p == pp) {
460 found = true;
461 break;
462 }
463 }
464 if (!found) {
465 allFound = false;
466 break;
467 }
468 }
469 if (allFound) {
470 // the row 'r' contain all the pairs from 'pairs'
471 return true;
472 }
473 }
474 return false;
475}
476
477// Remove all the rows that contains only specified pairs
478static void
479RemovePartialRows(std::list<ExpandedRow>& rows, const std::list<ExpandedPair>& pairs)
480{
481 auto it = rows.begin();
482 while (it != rows.end()) {
483 //ExpandedRow r = iterator.next();
484 if (it->pairs().size() == pairs.size()) {
485 ++it;
486 continue;
487 }
488 bool allFound = true;
489 for (const ExpandedPair& p : it->pairs()) {
490 bool found = false;
491 for (const ExpandedPair& pp : pairs) {
492 if (p == pp) {
493 found = true;
494 break;
495 }
496 }
497 if (!found) {
498 allFound = false;
499 break;
500 }
501 }
502 if (allFound) {
503 // 'pairs' contains all the pairs from the row 'r'
504 auto remPos = it;
505 ++it;
506 rows.erase(remPos);
507 }
508 else {
509 ++it;
510 }
511 }
512}
513
514static void
515StoreRow(std::list<ExpandedRow>& rows, const std::list<ExpandedPair>& pairs, int rowNumber, bool wasReversed)
516{
517 // Discard if duplicate above or below; otherwise insert in order by row number.
518 bool prevIsSame = false;
519 bool nextIsSame = false;
520 auto insertPos = rows.begin();
521 for (; insertPos != rows.end(); ++insertPos) {
522 if (insertPos->rowNumber() > rowNumber) {
523 nextIsSame = insertPos->isEquivalent(pairs);
524 break;
525 }
526 prevIsSame = insertPos->isEquivalent(pairs);
527 }
528 if (nextIsSame || prevIsSame) {
529 return;
530 }
531
532 // When the row was partially decoded (e.g. 2 pairs found instead of 3),
533 // it will prevent us from detecting the barcode.
534 // Try to merge partial rows
535
536 // Check whether the row is part of an allready detected row
537 if (IsPartialRow(pairs, rows)) {
538 return;
539 }
540
541 rows.insert(insertPos, ExpandedRow(pairs, rowNumber, wasReversed));
542
543 RemovePartialRows(rows, pairs);
544}
545
546// Whether the pairs form a valid find pattern seqience,
547// either complete or a prefix
548static bool
549IsValidSequence(const std::list<ExpandedPair>& pairs)
550{
551 for (auto& sequence : FINDER_PATTERN_SEQUENCES) {
552 if (pairs.size() <= sequence.size() && std::equal(pairs.begin(), pairs.end(), sequence.begin(), [](const ExpandedPair& p, int seq) { return p.finderPattern().value() == seq; })) {
553 return true;
554 }
555 }
556 return false;
557}
558
559// Try to construct a valid rows sequence
560// Recursion is used to implement backtracking
561template <typename RowIterator>
562static std::list<ExpandedPair>
563CheckRows(RowIterator currentRow, RowIterator endRow, const std::list<ExpandedRow>& collectedRows)
564{
565 std::list<ExpandedPair> collectedPairs;
566 for (const auto& collectedRow : collectedRows) {
567 auto &p = collectedRow.pairs();
568 collectedPairs.insert(collectedPairs.end(), p.begin(), p.end());
569 }
570
571 for (; currentRow != endRow; ++currentRow) {
572 //ExpandedRow row = rows.get(i);
573 std::list<ExpandedPair> result = collectedPairs;
574 auto &p = currentRow->pairs();
575 result.insert(result.end(), p.begin(), p.end());
576
577 if (!IsValidSequence(result)) {
578 continue;
579 }
580
581 if (CheckChecksum(result)) {
582 return result;
583 }
584
585 std::list<ExpandedRow> rs = collectedRows;
586 rs.push_back(*currentRow);
587 auto nextRow = currentRow;
588 result = CheckRows(++nextRow, endRow, rs);
589 if (!result.empty()) {
590 return result;
591 }
592 }
593 return std::list<ExpandedPair>();
594}
595
596static std::list<ExpandedPair>
597CheckRows(std::list<ExpandedRow>& rows, bool reverse) {
598 // Limit number of rows we are checking
599 // We use recursive algorithm with pure complexity and don't want it to take forever
600 // Stacked barcode can have up to 11 rows, so 25 seems reasonable enough
601 if (rows.size() > 25) {
602 rows.clear(); // We will never have a chance to get result, so clear it
603 return std::list<ExpandedPair>();
604 }
605
606 return reverse ?
607 CheckRows(rows.rbegin(), rows.rend(), std::list<ExpandedRow>()) :
608 CheckRows(rows.begin(), rows.end(), std::list<ExpandedRow>());
609}

611// Not private for testing
612static std::list<ExpandedPair>
613DecodeRow2Pairs(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, bool startFromEven, std::list<ExpandedRow>& rows)
614{
615 std::list<ExpandedPair> pairs;
616 ExpandedPair nextPair;
617 while (RetrieveNextPair(row, pairs, rowNumber, startFromEven, nextPair)) {
618 pairs.push_back(nextPair);
619 }
620
621 if (pairs.empty()) {
622 return pairs;
623 }
624
625 // TODO: verify sequence of finder patterns as in checkPairSequence()
626 if (CheckChecksum(pairs)) {
627 return pairs;
628 }
629
630 bool tryStackedDecode = !rows.empty();
631 bool wasReversed = false; // TODO: deal with reversed rows
632 StoreRow(rows, pairs, rowNumber, wasReversed);
633 if (tryStackedDecode) {
634 // When the image is 180-rotated, then rows are sorted in wrong direction.
635 // Try twice with both the directions.
636 auto ps = CheckRows(rows, false);
637 if (!ps.empty()) {
638 return ps;
639 }
640 ps = CheckRows(rows, true);
641 if (!ps.empty()) {
642 return ps;
643 }
644 }
645 return std::list<ExpandedPair>();
646}
647
648/**
649* @author Pablo Orduña, University of Deusto (pablo.orduna@deusto.es)
650* @author Eduardo Castillejo, University of Deusto (eduardo.castillejo@deusto.es)
651*/
652static BitArray
653BuildBitArray(const std::list<ExpandedPair>& pairs)
654{
655 int charNumber = (Size(pairs) * 2) - 1;
656 if (pairs.back().mustBeLast()) {
657 charNumber -= 1;
658 }
659
660 BitArray result(12 * charNumber);
661 int accPos = 0;
662 auto it = pairs.begin();
663 int firstValue = it->rightChar().value();
664 for (int i = 11; i >= 0; --i) {
665 if ((firstValue & (1 << i)) != 0) {
666 result.set(accPos);
667 }
668 accPos++;
669 }
670
671 for (++it; it != pairs.end(); ++it) {
672 int leftValue = it->leftChar().value();
673 for (int j = 11; j >= 0; --j) {
674 if ((leftValue & (1 << j)) != 0) {
675 result.set(accPos);
676 }
677 accPos++;
678 }
679
680 if (it->rightChar().isValid()) {
681 int rightValue = it->rightChar().value();
682 for (int j = 11; j >= 0; --j) {
683 if ((rightValue & (1 << j)) != 0) {
684 result.set(accPos);
685 }
686 accPos++;
687 }
688 }
689 }
690 return result;
691}

693// Not private for unit testing
694static Result
695ConstructResult(const std::list<ExpandedPair>& pairs)
696{
697 if (pairs.empty()) {
698 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
699 }
700
701 BitArray binary = BuildBitArray(pairs);
702 auto resultString = ExpandedBinaryDecoder::Decode(binary);
703 if (resultString.empty()) {
704 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
705 }
706
707 auto& firstPoints = pairs.front().finderPattern().points();
708 auto& lastPoints = pairs.back().finderPattern().points();
709
710 return Result(TextDecoder::FromLatin1(resultString), { firstPoints[0], firstPoints[1], lastPoints[0], lastPoints[1] }, BarcodeFormat::RSS_EXPANDED);
711}
712
713Result
714RSSExpandedReader::decodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState>& state) const
715{
716 if (!state) {
717 state.reset(new RSSExpandedDecodingState);
718 }
719 auto* prevState = static_cast<RSSExpandedDecodingState*>(state.get());
720
721 // Rows can start with even pattern in case in prev rows there where odd number of patters.
722 // So lets try twice
723 Result r = ConstructResult(DecodeRow2Pairs(rowNumber, row, false, prevState->rows));
724 if (!r.isValid()) {
725 r = ConstructResult(DecodeRow2Pairs(rowNumber, row, true, prevState->rows));
726 }
727 return r;
728}
